This may include electronic mail (correspondence), case assessment documents, plans, notes, interview reports, health reports or application forms
readme:
Service Usage

An information record represents any electronic or hardcopy item of documentation or correspondence (correspondence encompasses any associated attachments). This may include electronic mail (correspondence), case assessment documents, plans, notes, interview reports, health reports or application forms
The service enables a consumer to select, retrieve and reserve an Information Record for modification.
In the context of the service, all information records fall into two distinct sub types, Document/Attachment and Primary Information Record Item. If the requested subtype is a Document/Attachment the service returns physical Information Record and its associated metadata. If the requested subtype is a Primary Information Record Item the service will return the Primary Information Record Item (contents) a list of associated attachment(s) and related metadata. The consumer may then choose to re-invoke the service to retrieve a specific record (attachment).

Service Behaviour

The execution of this service is a step that will allow VPO to view Information record list and then select a particular information record to view.

To invoke the service a consumer inputs:
Information Record Id ,
Checkout Requested Flag and

The Provider System responds with :
Metadata associated with content of the Information Record, or if applicable, metadata associated with associated attachments. Metadata includes the date and time the document was last updated and its edit status.
Content of the record (An electronic file of any type e.g. .txt, .doc, .pdf, .xls etc)
Business context associations(s)
Related record associations(s)
Container metadata (Id, type, location, paper file created flag if applicable)

Note: The service does not provide a complete historical audit trail of changes made to an information record. However this function is available through the existing TRIM user interface.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique information record Id. This service also expects that the meta-information provided with an information record will be record keeping compliant.

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other services within the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to RKS to retrieve information record.
The following service flow describes a successful execution path.

  1. Service Consumer invokes service on ESB with
    RetrieveInformationRecordRequest.
  2. ESB transforms RetrieveInformationRequest to RetrieveRecordRequest.
  3. ESB invokes RecordKeeping.RetrieveRecordRequest() on Record Keeping interface using RetrieveRecordRequest object.
  4. Record Keeping service returns RetrieveRecordResponse to ESB.
  5. Use Alternate flow 1 if Record keeping service raises Error
  6. ESB transforms RetrieveRecordResponse to RetrieveInformationResponse and returns response to the consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1
ESB transforms errors into enterprise error message and returns to the consumer. Please see the section Service Enterprise Return Code Message for more details.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
